PIN_BTN_DOWN (Pin 6): Decrements parameter selections.
PIN_BTN_START_RESET (Pin 7): Multi-functional input. A short press (<500ms) starts the sequence, pauses execution, or unpauses execution. A long press (>=1000ms) forces a soft reboot.
Servo Control Interfaces: Three digital outputs simulating mechanical button presses on the target bread maker (driven via temporary LOW state shifts acting as active-low open-collector simulators):
srvMenu (Pin 9): "Menu" switch wire.
srvMinus (Pin 10): "Minus/Adjustment" switch wire.
srvRunReset (Pin 11): "Start/Stop" switch wire.
Display: I2C Adafruit SSD1306 128x64 OLED display utilizing Adafruit_GFX and Wire libraries.
